			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm no expert but I think the Doom 3 shadows were made black on purpose for.. er.. Doom 3. It was meant to be a horror game that was supposedly scary so the pitch black was meant to make the player feel uneasy and afraid of the dark. Problem is you always knew that a zombie or whatever was going to appear out of the shadows so it just got annoying eventually. You can always turn the shadows off if you hate them that much, not only does it look better but you gain fps.</span><span class=sign><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v221/deathcrush/phead.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">They have come to witness the beginning, the rebirth of paradise...</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span>
                  <br /><br />
                  </td>
