				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What a pitty !!!
<br />
Such a powerfull feature...
<br />
I agree.. of course dynamic global illumination is still a 
<br />
thing for the next generations of harware. It압 even 
<br />
still a hard task to render with non-realtime renderer.
<br />
But I see no reason why to exclude static Lightcalculations from the engine.
<br />
Dynamic Lights and precalculated 
<br />
Lightmaps can easily work together... other engines prove that !!
<br />
I mean.. Quake and Doom look nice with all the details and effects...
<br />
But with lighmaps the realism could be increased drastically. 
<br />
Especially the outdoor levels look just terrible (
<br />
a lighting artists point of view)
<br />
And it looks they didn앖 even include a standard ambient light
<br />
(otherwise an ambient light tutorial wouldn앖 be neccessary ?!)
<br />
The last time I rendered and illuminated scenes like this is probabely 10 years ago !! Things like that I would expect from EA Games.. but not from ID... shaking head...
