				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To be honest sam, using lightmaps is a rather old technique and the doom 3 engine is going into the right direction of games, completely rendered in real-time.
<br />

<br />
But you are right that they took this step probably a little bit too early.
<br />

<br />
Nevertheless, this engine is made for Doom. It is made for a dark atmosphere, where pitch black shadows only support the whole scary theme.
<br />

<br />
I suppose that is one reason why every game on that engine got this so called "Doom 3" look (I guess Prey will be similiar).
<br />

<br />
I also agree on your opinion on the outdoor maps. But Quake Wars looked really promising, they are obviously working on a new way to light terrain stuff. We앏l see <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />.</span><span class=sign></span><span class="gensmall"></span>
                  <br /><br />
